# CORE — Grain v6

## Product Identity

Grain is an action-based reflection system.

It protects intentional living by revealing whether weekly actions align with declared direction.

It does not:
- Gamify
- Reward streaks
- Penalize missed days
- Compare users
- Optimize productivity

It reveals patterns.

---

## Core Philosophy

- Users already know their destination.
- Time is life capital.
- Drift is information, not failure.
- Recalibration is normal.
- Unlogged ≠ zero.
- Progress compounds through steady consistency.

Grain lives between discipline and awareness.

---

## Architectural Guardrails

The data model is action-based and event-driven.

- Logging is stored as individual events.
- Never aggregate before storing.
- Aggregation happens in queries, not inserts.
- Never reintroduce `support_definition`.
- Execution strategy is represented via `journey_actions`.

---

## Tone Rules

- Short lines.
- Second person.
- Questions over commands.
- No exclamation marks.
- No motivational language.
- No gamification vocabulary.

Never introduce:
- Streaks
- Badges
- Leaderboards
- Performance optimization language
- Competitive metrics

Grain is honest, steady, enduring.